  </sponsors>
  <source>Chinese University of Hong Kong</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Spastic esophageal motility disorders induced significant symptoms including dysphagia,
      retrosternal pain and regurgitation. Per oral endoscopic myotomy (P.O.E.M.) is a novel
      approach to perform myotomy through the esophagus with long submucosal tunnel. This study
      aimed to investigate the feasibility and safety of P.O.E.M. and translate the techniques
      from animal study to clinical practice in human.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
